      "message": "An availability zone (in Nova) is a a tag for a host aggregate. Take a look at [1]. You can \"split\" the hosts in host aggregates and then, if you want, assign a AZ to those HA.\n\nA placement group is just a way to define, using the SameHostAffinityFilter, where to spawn the VM. In Yardstick we can define, for a placement group, [\"affinity\", \"availability\"]:\n- Affinity: try to spawn the VMs in the same host\n- Availability: just the opposite\n\n[1] https://www.mirantis.com/blog/the-first-and-final-word-on-openstack-availability-zones/",
